  "notes": "Proto-Munda (~4000–3000 BCE). Reconstructed common ancestor of all Munda languages (Santali, Mundari, Ho, Korku, Kharia, Sora). Austroasiatic > Munda branch. Sesquisyllabic word structure; register/phonation contrast; no tones; rich onset clusters; no retroflexes at proto-stage. Refs: Pinnow (1959), Anderson (2008), Donegan & Stampe (2004).",
